post_cb({"16595715": {"CreationDate": "2013-05-16T19:21:09.593", "ViewCount": "470", "Id": "16595715", "AcceptedAnswerId": "16595788", "Score": "7", "Title": "Brace initialization for class with virtual function", "LastEditorUserId": "1409312", "CommentCount": "2", "Body": "<p>There is this code:</p>\n<pre><code>struct A {\n   int x;\n   void f() {}\n};\n\nstruct B {\n   int y;\n   virtual void f() {}\n};\n\nA a = {2};\n\n//B b = {3}; error: no matching constructor for initialization of 'B'\n\nint main() {\n   return 0;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Why initialization for variable <code>a</code> works but not for variable <code>b</code>?</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><c++11>", "LastEditDate": "2013-05-16T19:44:52.903", "LastActivityDate": "2013-05-16T19:44:52.903", "PostTypeId": "1", "AnswerCount": "1", "OwnerUserId": "738811"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_16595715_16595788_0": {"length": 16, "quality": 0.6666666666666666, "section_id": 3298}}, "n3337": {"so_16595715_16595788_0": {"length": 19, "quality": 0.7916666666666666, "section_id": 3168}}}, "16595788": {"CommentCount": "6", "Body": "<p><code>A</code> is an aggregate, and so can have brace initialization, and <code>B</code> isn't, since it has a virtual method.</p>\n<p><strong>8.5.1 Aggregates</strong></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_16595715_16595788_0\">An aggregate is an array or a class (Clause 9) with no user-provided constructors (12.1), no brace-or-equal-\n  initializers for non-static data members (9.2), no private or protected non-static data members (Clause 11),\n  no base classes (Clause 10), and no virtual functions (10.3).</p>\n</blockquote>\n", "CreationDate": "2013-05-16T19:25:13.417", "ParentId": "16595715", "Id": "16595788", "LastActivityDate": "2013-05-16T19:25:13.417", "PostTypeId": "2", "Score": "10", "OwnerUserId": "661519"}});